A former Lagos State Governor and presidential aspirant, Bola Tinubu, on Tuesday night visited the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), at his official residence in the Presidential Villa, Abuja. This was announced by the president’s Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, on his Facebook page. Adesina also shared pictures of the visit. He captioned the pictures, “President Muhammadu Buhari receives Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu at the Villa on Tuesday night…May 3rd 2022.” See photos below:  Photos: Sunday Aghaeze Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com